      <p style="text-align: center;"><em>Chocolate Cake with silky chocolate frosting</em></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Ingredients</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>1 and 1/2 cups (190g) all-purpose flour (maida)</li>
        <li>1 cup (200g) granulated sugar</li>
        <li>1/2 cup (45g) unsweetened cocoa powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp baking powder and 1/2 tsp baking soda</li>
        <li>1/4 tsp salt and 2 large eggs</li>
        <li>1/2 cup (120ml) vegetable oil or melted butter</li>
        <li>1 cup (240ml) milk and 1 tsp vanilla extract</li>
        <li>1/2 cup (120ml) hot water</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Frosting (Chocolate Ganache)</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1/2 cup (120ml) heavy cream</li>
            <li>100g dark chocolate, chopped</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Method</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 180°C (350°F). Grease and line a cake tin.</li>
        <li>In a large mixing bowl, sift together flour, cocoa powder, baking powder, baking soda, and salt.</li>
        <li>In another bowl, whisk eggs, sugar, milk, oil, and vanilla extract until smooth.</li>
        <li>Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients and mix until just combined.</li>
        <li>Slowly pour in hot water and mix gently — the batter will be thin (that’s good for a moist cake!).</li>
        <li>Pour the batter into the prepared tin. Bake for 30–35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.</li>
        <li>Heat the cream in a pan (do not boil), then pour over the chopped chocolate. Let sit for 1–2 minutes. Stir until smooth. Let it cool slightly, then spread over the cake.</li>
      </ol>
